'''Kōto Ōji''' is one of the {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|fr|Kujūkuōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=99 ōji Shrines|12=draft}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]]. <!--subst:PAGENAME magic word should be substituted in the future when this is moved to its final pagename. This was added to a few pages not created on Feb 8 because they were very barren and this gives context to the fact that they are in a large group of pages all to be translated more or less as a group similar to the Ise Shrines--> ==Overview== [[File:Kozu-Gu Himekoso-jinja Koto-oji.JPG|thumb|280px|{{ill|Himekoso Shrine|ja|比売古曽神社|12=draft}}, a subsidiary shrine of {{ill|Kōzu Shrine|ja|高津宮|1=Kōzu-gū|12=draft}}, believed to be the site of Kōto Ōji]] '''Kōto Ōji''' ('''こうとおうじ''') was the third {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|12=draft}} shrine along the {{ill|Kumano Kodo|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|12=draft}} pilgrimage route. The shrine no longer exists. The site is believed to be where {{ill|Kōzu Shrine|ja|高津宮|1=Kōzu-gū|12=draft}} is currently located, in {{ill|Chūō-ku, Osaka|ja|中央区 (大阪市)|12=draft}}, {{ill|Osaka City|ja|大阪市|12=draft}} (1-1-29 Kōzu), though there is no definitive proof.
According to the historical text ''{{ill|Settsu-shi|ja|摂津志|12=draft}}'', the {{ill|Himekoso Shrine|ja|比売許曽神社|12=draft}}, which once stood at the current location of Kōzu Shrine, was regarded as the Kōto Ōji.
== Nearest Station == * {{ill|Tanimachi Kyūchōme Station|ja|谷町九丁目駅|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Osaka Metro Tanimachi Line|ja|Osaka Metro谷町線|12=draft}}
