le/Kumano Hongū Taisha|qq=}}） | style="background:#ccffcc" |[[湯の峰王子|湯ノ峯王子]] goodbye $1（{{ill|Kumano Hayatama Taisha|ja|熊野速玉大社|lt=Hayatama Taisha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Hayatama Taisha|qq=}}） | style="background:#ccffcc" |[[浜王子]] | style="background:#ccffcc" |[[佐野王子 (新宮市)|佐野王子]] | style="background:#ccffcc" |[[熊野三所大神社|浜の宮王子]] |- | style="background:#ccffcc" |[[市野々王子]] | style="background:#ccffcc" |[[多富気王子]] goodbye $1（{{ill|--><!-- | style="background:#ccffcc" |[[九十九王子 (日高町)#小中王子|小中王子]] | style="background:#ccffcc" |[[九十九王子 (日高町)#比井王子|比井王子]] | style="background:#ccffcc" |[[九十九王子 (日高町)#松原王子|松原王子]] --> [[Category:pages needing proper jawiki and history import]]

'''Kōto Ōji''' is one of the {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|fr|Kujūku Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=99 ōji Shrines|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|qq=}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]].
==Overview== [[File:Kozu-Gu Himekoso-jinja Koto-oji.JPG|thumb|280px|{{ill|Himekoso Shrine|ja|比売古曽神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Himekoso Shrine|qq=}}, a subsidiary shrine of {{ill|Kōzu Shrine|ja|高津宮|1=Kōzu-gū|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōzu Shrine|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōzu-gū|qq=}}, believed to be the site of Kōto Ōji]] '''Kōto Ōji''' ('''郡戸王子''') was the third {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|1=Kujūku Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|qq=}} shrine along the {{ill|Kumano Kodo|ja|熊野古道|1=Kumano Kodō|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kodo|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kodō|qq=}} pilgrimage route. The shrine no longer exists. The site is believed to be where {{ill|Kōzu Shrine|ja|高津宮|1=Kōzu-gū|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōzu Shrine|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōzu-gū|qq=}} is currently located, in {{ill|Chūō-ku, Osaka|ja|中央区 (大阪市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chūō-ku, Osaka|qq=}}, {{ill|Osaka City|ja|大阪市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka City|qq=}} (1-1-29 Kōzu), though there is no definitive proof.
According to the historical text ''{{ill|Settsu-shi|ja|摂津志|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Settsu-shi|qq=}}'', the {{ill|Himekoso Shrine|ja|比売許曽神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Himekoso Shrine|qq=}}, which once stood at the current location of Kōzu Shrine, was regarded as the Kōto Ōji.
== Nearest Station == * {{ill|Tanimachi Kyūchōme Station|ja|谷町九丁目駅|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanimachi Kyūchōme Station|qq=}} on the {{ill|Osaka Metro Tanimachi Line|ja|Osaka Metro谷町線|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka Metro Tanimachi Line|qq=}}
