'''Kōto Ōji''' is one of the {{ill|Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|fr|Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|ja|九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|lt=99 ōji Shrines|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|qq=}} on the [[Kumano Kodō]].
==Overview== [[File:Kozu-Gu Himekoso-jinja Koto-oji.JPG|thumb|280px|{{ill|Himekoso Shrine|ja|比売古曽神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Himekoso Shrine|qq=}}, a subsidiary shrine of [[:en:Kōzu-gū|Kōzu-gū]], believed to be the site of Kōto Ōji]] '''Kōto Ōji''' ('''郡戸王子''') was the third {{ill|Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|ja|九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|2=ja|3=九十九王子|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|4=fr|5=Kujūkuōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|1=Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Kyuju-kū Ōji|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujūku Ōji|lt=Ninety-Nine Ōji|qq=}} shrine along the [[:en:Kumano Kodō|Kumano Kodō]] pilgrimage route. The shrine no longer exists. The site is believed to be where [[:en:Kōzu-gū|Kōzu-gū]] is currently located, in [[:en:Chūō-ku, Osaka|Chūō-ku, Osaka]], [[:en:Osaka|Osaka City]] (1-1-29 Kōzu), though there is no definitive proof.
According to the historical text ''{{ill|Settsu-shi|ja|摂津志|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Settsu-shi|qq=}}'', the {{ill|Himekoso Shrine|ja|比売許曽神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Himekoso Shrine|qq=}}, which once stood at the current location of Kōzu Shrine, was regarded as the Kōto Ōji.
== Nearest Station == * [[:en:Tanimachi Kyūchōme Station|Tanimachi Kyūchōme Station]] on the [[:en:Tanimachi Line|Osaka Metro Tanimachi Line]]
